The operation saw officers storm a house in Lenasia South outside Johannesburg on Wednesday night.Hawks spokesman Captain Ndivhuwo Mulamu said officers from the South African Narcotics Enforcement Bureau and Crime Intelligence received information on the operation of the clandestine laboratory.He said the lab was allegedly used to process gold and platinum."When officers raided the house they discovered unprocessed gold gold concentrate material gold nuggets unprocessed platinum and refined platinum as well as the manufacturing equipment valued at R5 million."He said a 31-year-old man was arrested on charges of illegally manufacturing precious metals.The man is to appear in the Protea Magistrate's Court on Friday.